Ahead of  tomorrow’s GOtv Boxing Night 25 at the Old Gymnasium of the Obafemi Awolowo Stadium in Ibadan, boxers scheduled to fight have been talking tough. The show, regarded as the continent’s biggest boxing platform, will feature seven fights in different weight categories. Onitsha-based  Victor Bennet is upbeat about his chances of winning his lightweight bout against Segun “Success” Olanrewaju as the Anambra dynamite insisted  that Olanrewaju’s foreign experience will count for nothing when they face each other. “I know Olanrewaju recently returned from a fight in Russia but that will mean nothing on Saturday’s night because I will beat him without mercy,” he bragged. “I promise that his nickname will change to ‘failure’.”   WAFU B Tourney: Ugbade promises ‘superb’  Golden Eaglets     Rudiger joins Real Madrid from Chelsea on free transfer     2021/2022 UEFA Champions league team   But Olanrewaju fired back,  promising to teach his opponent a big lesson in the ring. “Bennet has been running his mouth but talk is cheap; I won’t talk too much and I will leave the rest to my fists,” he said. Meanwhile, heavyweight boxer Solomon Imole has said he can’t wait to crush Olanrewaju “Larry King” Adebiyi against whom he is scheduled to fight. Reacting to Adebiyi’s eagerness to fight him, Imole said his opponent will end the day regretting his decision to take him on . Also speaking ahead of his fight with Ibadan-based lightweight boxer, Samuel “Apata Roro” Moses, lightweight boxer, Wale Anifowoshe has told his opponent to expect humiliation in front of his supporters.